-- Colombia Stock Movers: Bancolombia, Banco de Bogota, Canacol
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-01-05T21:16:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-05/colombia-stock-movers-bancolombia-banco-de-bogota-canacol.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 0.3 percent to 12,972.03, while the
Colcap Index was little changed at 1,606.09.  Bank lending continued to expand at a slower pace in
December,  Colombia ’s central bank said in its monthly  report  on
credit published Jan. 2.  Bancolombia SA (PFBCOLO)  (BCOLO CB), Colombia’s biggest lender, fell
for a fourth day, declining 0.1 percent to 28,380 pesos.  Banco de Bogota SA (BOGOTA)  , the nation’s second-biggest
lender, slid 0.3 percent to 49,700 pesos.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)   climbed 7.7 percent to 1,545
pesos. The Calgary-based  oil company  that operates fields in
Colombia has jumped 30 percent since Dec. 27, the day before
saying in a statement that it completed the drilling of an oil
well in the Rancho Hermoso field and that it is “fully
financed” to carry out its 2012 plan of 14 exploration and 26
development wells.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
